WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

02:06.408 --> 02:07.742
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

02:15.042 --> 02:18.169
MAN: I think he's inside.
I'm gonna check it out.

02:18.337 --> 02:20.588
MAN OVER RADIO: Burke, wait for backup.

02:20.756 --> 02:24.300
BURKE:
He killed my partner. I'm not waiting.

02:24.468 --> 02:28.679
RADIO: Listen, Burke, this is LA,
not Canada. We have procedures here.

02:28.847 --> 02:30.723
You can't handle this alone.

02:34.353 --> 02:37.230
- What's the problem?
- Hey, man. What you doing here?

02:37.397 --> 02:39.482
I'm busy. Scram.

02:39.650 --> 02:41.776
I'm gonna teach you a lesson in manners.

02:45.364 --> 02:48.157
- I'm gonna get you, man!
- Like I said, I'm going in.

02:48.325 --> 02:49.826
RADIO: Burke... Burke!

03:25.404 --> 03:27.697
[WATER DRIPPING]

03:48.302 --> 03:50.178
[WIND CHIMES JINGLE]

04:36.350 --> 04:37.725
[SCREAMS]

04:37.893 --> 04:39.810
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

04:41.271 --> 04:42.313
[GROWLS]

04:43.398 --> 04:45.358
- [GROWLS]
- [GRUNTS]

04:48.403 --> 04:52.531
Time to go to sleep...
and join your old partner.

04:56.620 --> 05:00.498
I'm the Sandman. You can't stop me.

05:02.042 --> 05:03.209
[GRUNTS]

05:10.008 --> 05:12.760
[POLICE SIRENS BLARING]

05:12.928 --> 05:14.553
[SIGHS]

05:15.806 --> 05:16.847
[TIRES SCREECHING]

05:17.015 --> 05:18.975
You're under arrest.

06:17.326 --> 06:19.493
Detective Burke. Have a seat.

06:22.873 --> 06:24.790
Tom Vogler, attorney general.

06:24.958 --> 06:28.044
On my right is Ben Keane,
on your left is Sam Walden.

06:28.211 --> 06:31.505
I represent the governor.
I'm heading his task force on prisons.

06:31.673 --> 06:34.050
I'm with the State Board of Corrections.

06:34.718 --> 06:37.470
- And who are you?
- VOGLER: Amanda Beckett.

06:37.637 --> 06:39.013
She works for me.

06:39.181 --> 06:42.516
Detective Burke specialized
in undercover work

06:42.684 --> 06:46.395
with the Royal Canadian Mounted Police
stationed in Quebec.

06:46.855 --> 06:49.815
You followed Christian Naylor,
the Sandman, to LA.

06:50.984 --> 06:54.362
We've had problems in one of
our prisons: Harrison Penitentiary.

06:54.529 --> 06:56.572
It's a local piece, small-town news.

06:58.283 --> 06:59.867
KEANE: The assistant warden was murdered.

07:00.035 --> 07:01.952
Now a guard has intimated

07:02.120 --> 07:04.747
that it might be linked
to the deaths of some prisoners.

07:04.915 --> 07:06.749
Nine in the last few months.

07:06.917 --> 07:10.586
We've got a gubernatorial election
coming up this fall.

07:10.754 --> 07:13.964
Prisons are already an issue.
We don't want this to be part of it.

07:14.132 --> 07:17.843
The governor has put me in charge
of rectifying this little mishap.

07:18.887 --> 07:22.098
We wanna send you undercover
into Harrison as a prisoner.

07:26.144 --> 07:29.480
VOGLER: You're from Quebec.
No one in jail will recognize you.

07:29.648 --> 07:33.442
Only we will know you're an officer.
You'll be sentenced for armed robbery.

07:33.610 --> 07:36.695
KEANE: Armed robbery is
a respectable crime among inmates.

07:36.863 --> 07:40.741
It's implicitly violent.
They respect violence.

07:40.909 --> 07:42.993
We're also assigning a partner of sorts.

07:43.161 --> 07:47.123
VOGLER: Amanda will act as your liaison.
She'll be posing as your wife.

07:47.290 --> 07:49.625
Amanda will relay information.
Through her,

07:49.793 --> 07:52.962
we will closely monitor the operation.

07:56.091 --> 07:58.676
Well, Detective? What d'you say?

08:03.682 --> 08:05.057
I'll let you know.

08:06.977 --> 08:10.062
[THUNDERING]

08:10.230 --> 08:12.815
AMANDA:
Would you like me to file those papers?

08:12.983 --> 08:16.152
VOGLER: The sooner the better.
You always do a good job.

08:16.319 --> 08:20.281
- So we'll see you tomorrow night?
- Have Helen call if she wants anything.

08:20.449 --> 08:22.658
- I will.
- OK. Bye.

08:22.826 --> 08:24.660
A pleasure meeting you, Mr. Burke.

08:26.163 --> 08:28.998
- How long have you known him?
- A long time.

08:29.166 --> 08:31.459
He's like a father to me.

08:31.626 --> 08:33.669
I've been working for him
ever since I graduated law school.

08:33.837 --> 08:35.087
When was that?

08:36.006 --> 08:37.381
Last year.

08:41.510 --> 08:43.721
Is there a problem, Detective Burke?

08:44.598 --> 08:47.224
You don't have enough experience
to be on this case.

08:48.310 --> 08:50.895
Let's get something straight here,
Detective.

08:51.688 --> 08:56.358
I'm no girl Friday.
I graduated top in my class at Stanford.

08:56.526 --> 08:59.111
If you're uncomfortable with the fact
that I'm a woman,

08:59.279 --> 09:01.030
it's your problem, not mine.

09:02.032 --> 09:07.244
OK. Check the files of
any serial killers at Harrison prison.

09:08.163 --> 09:09.997
Then you'll take the case?

09:11.833 --> 09:13.751
- I'll see you Tuesday.
- [THUNDERCLAP]

09:15.045 --> 09:16.504
I'll get to work.

09:20.509 --> 09:21.509
Louis...

09:25.013 --> 09:26.347
you're getting wet.

09:37.275 --> 09:39.276
[CHATTERING]

10:02.175 --> 10:05.094
[CATCALLS, WHISTLING]

10:19.359 --> 10:22.444
[CHEERING, WHISTLING]

10:37.335 --> 10:38.794
Listen up!

10:40.088 --> 10:43.674
Clasp your fingers in front of you.

10:47.137 --> 10:48.804
And don't move.

10:50.640 --> 10:53.434
I am Sergeant DeGraf.

10:55.520 --> 10:57.938
I decide when you eat...

10:58.898 --> 11:00.858
when you shower...

11:01.026 --> 11:03.402
when you have visitors.

11:03.695 --> 11:06.405
You are fish.

11:06.823 --> 11:08.616
New arrivals.

11:10.327 --> 11:12.620
People will try to hurt you...

11:13.538 --> 11:15.039
rob you...

11:20.170 --> 11:21.545
even rape you.

11:30.889 --> 11:31.930
[GROANS]

11:39.731 --> 11:41.649
He said "don't move".

11:43.443 --> 11:45.277
Very good.

11:49.532 --> 11:54.370
It's important that you obey my rules.

12:05.965 --> 12:10.678
Rules can make the difference
between your life and your death.

12:14.432 --> 12:17.810
I'm Dr. Gottesman.
Any communicable diseases?

12:17.977 --> 12:19.061
Not yet.

12:20.730 --> 12:21.980
Excuse me?

12:23.733 --> 12:25.442
You're Burke, right?

12:28.196 --> 12:31.240
You have AB-negative blood.
That's very rare.

12:31.908 --> 12:36.161
OK, take it into the next room, please.
Come on, move it.

12:43.545 --> 12:46.505
MAN: Your identification number is 72688.

12:46.673 --> 12:49.425
Memorize your number: 72688.

12:49.592 --> 12:52.720
This is your identification card,
Mr. 72688.

12:52.887 --> 12:57.141
Your new home is C level, cell C-71. Next!

13:03.648 --> 13:05.983
- It's dead.
- Excuse me?

13:06.151 --> 13:09.611
The eye. You were looking at it.
It's dead.

13:09.779 --> 13:12.281
- Got stabbed in it.
- Stabbed in the eye?

13:14.033 --> 13:16.410
Yeah, I got stabbed in the eye.

13:18.037 --> 13:19.955
4:27.

13:20.123 --> 13:23.041
OK, you got your towel,
you got your toothbrush.

13:23.209 --> 13:25.794
Meal shift starts every morning at 6:10.

13:25.962 --> 13:29.089
Lunch is noon straight up,
dinner's at 6:30pm.

13:29.257 --> 13:33.802
You can take a shower once a day. Check
for fungus and body lice. Any questions?

13:34.471 --> 13:37.347
Your identification number is 72689.

13:37.515 --> 13:39.933
Memorize your number: 72689.

13:40.101 --> 13:43.479
72689. Right. My name is Burke.

13:44.564 --> 13:46.648
That's your ID card, Mr. 72689.

13:46.816 --> 13:50.486
Your new home is C level, cell C-68. Next!

13:50.653 --> 13:51.820
Thanks.

13:54.991 --> 13:58.911
OK, you've got your towel,
you've got your toothbrush...

13:59.078 --> 14:01.038
[CHATTERING]

14:28.483 --> 14:30.692
[RADIO STATIC]

14:37.867 --> 14:38.867
[RADIO CLICKS OFF]

14:48.127 --> 14:52.089
What're ya doin' here?
And whaddaya think you're lookin' at?

14:53.049 --> 14:54.424
I'm new here.

14:55.051 --> 14:57.928
I don't care what you are.
You think you can just sleep here?

14:58.888 --> 15:02.224
Real estate. Cost you $500.

15:04.060 --> 15:08.063
- Don't have any money.
- Oh, you don't have any money.

15:08.231 --> 15:10.065
Well, that's OK.

15:11.776 --> 15:12.901
You can punk.

15:14.070 --> 15:14.987
Excuse me?

15:15.154 --> 15:16.321
[SCOFFS]

15:17.490 --> 15:19.533
You get down on your hands and knees...

15:20.535 --> 15:24.204
and you pay, just like any other cherry.

15:26.249 --> 15:30.419
- I don't think so.
- Oh... you don't think so?

15:33.006 --> 15:36.133
Possibly... you might wanna reconsider.

15:37.927 --> 15:39.511
[GROANS]

15:42.140 --> 15:44.308
I don't pay, I don't punk.

15:44.976 --> 15:47.185
OK, OK, take it easy.

15:47.353 --> 15:50.314
I was jerkin' you around.
Don't have a hairball about it.

15:50.481 --> 15:53.358
Look, you want the top bunk? Take it.

15:53.526 --> 15:56.153
- The bottom one would be nice.
- You got it.

15:56.321 --> 15:57.321
Thanks.

15:59.657 --> 16:00.824
[BELL RINGS]

16:08.416 --> 16:10.250
[CHATTERING]

16:17.300 --> 16:20.719
- 72689, remember?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, I remember.

16:21.679 --> 16:23.096
You don't wanna eat that.

16:24.098 --> 16:25.265
What's wrong with my food?

16:28.102 --> 16:29.436
Hey, nigger...

16:29.604 --> 16:32.856
Are you talking about me, ese, huh?

16:33.816 --> 16:35.943
Perez, we keep to ourselves now.

16:36.110 --> 16:38.695
- We don't give a shit about you people.
- Oh, yeah?

16:38.863 --> 16:41.615
- Hey, listen, let him go.
- Hey, it's on me!

16:41.783 --> 16:43.700
- Let him go.
- It's cool, ese.

16:48.289 --> 16:49.957
[ALL YELLING]

16:51.042 --> 16:52.876
Fuckin' kill you, man!

16:53.044 --> 16:55.170
You dead, ese! Puto!

16:58.132 --> 17:01.468
You fuckin' dead, ese! You dead!

17:02.720 --> 17:04.346
Let me go, homeys.

17:06.557 --> 17:07.974
[CROWD QUIETS]

17:23.992 --> 17:26.034
I'll talk to you later.

17:29.372 --> 17:30.706
Hawkins.

17:35.837 --> 17:38.964
I know. Always the nigger's fault.

17:47.557 --> 17:49.975
You're not gonna last too long.

17:50.935 --> 17:53.645
- Is that a threat?
- No.

17:55.815 --> 17:57.983
It's a promise.

18:05.116 --> 18:07.492
It never happened!

18:07.660 --> 18:09.661
Back to dinner!

18:12.623 --> 18:14.291
[CHATTERING CONTINUES]

18:17.920 --> 18:20.297
You're a rata, ese.

18:20.465 --> 18:22.174
Fuckin' dead.

18:23.593 --> 18:25.677
Puto!

18:36.439 --> 18:41.068
What's the matter with you?
Can't you see this is a black table?

18:44.072 --> 18:48.158
Stick with your own kind.
Trust no one now.

18:48.659 --> 18:51.745
- What about you?
- What about me?

18:53.331 --> 18:54.956
You don't know who I am.

18:56.751 --> 18:58.418
You don't know anything.

18:59.629 --> 19:01.171
MAN: Hey, fish!

19:04.092 --> 19:06.468
Hey, why don't you sit with us, fish?

19:25.321 --> 19:26.863
Sit down, bright boy.

19:32.870 --> 19:36.039
- So what are you in for, huh?
- I was a bad boy.

19:36.207 --> 19:37.624
Aw...

19:37.792 --> 19:39.167
And you?

19:39.794 --> 19:44.840
Me and Keel here,
we got "the big bitch": habitual.

19:47.260 --> 19:48.552
See these?

19:52.765 --> 19:55.183
Those are the people he's killed.

19:56.519 --> 19:58.436
That's very special.

20:03.109 --> 20:04.651
[BELL RINGS]

20:05.194 --> 20:06.820
Rack 'em up, Jack!

20:10.491 --> 20:11.741
[ALARM BUZZES]

20:15.580 --> 20:17.122
Begin count.

20:17.290 --> 20:21.626
Tier 2-C, 69.

20:23.087 --> 20:25.046
Tier 2-C, 68.

20:25.214 --> 20:27.674
[ROLL CALL CONTINUES]

20:32.930 --> 20:34.264
[WHEEZES]

20:36.809 --> 20:38.059
Pruno.

20:40.229 --> 20:41.605
We make it ourselves.

20:56.913 --> 20:58.371
[CACKLES]

21:00.208 --> 21:02.209
Ah, it's good for what ails ya.

21:04.337 --> 21:07.214
Saw ya helpin' out that nigger, Hawkins.

21:08.466 --> 21:10.884
Not good. It's bad mojo.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.928
Most times you can't even trust
your own kind in this place,

21:13.095 --> 21:14.387
you know what I mean?

21:23.856 --> 21:25.315
Hey, Konefke...

21:27.318 --> 21:29.152
how long have you been here?

21:32.990 --> 21:35.075
Maybe... six years.

21:40.414 --> 21:43.541
I hear a lot of guys are dying.

21:48.089 --> 21:49.464
Konefke?

21:52.176 --> 21:53.635
Yeah, maybe.

21:54.845 --> 21:56.805
But I don't see so well no more.

21:58.099 --> 22:00.558
Like one of those monkeys you hear about.

22:01.894 --> 22:04.688
Hear no evil, see no evil.

22:17.994 --> 22:21.496
- [BABY CRIES]
- [FEMALE SPEAKS SPANISH]

22:22.290 --> 22:24.958
[MAN SPEAKING SPANISH]

22:26.794 --> 22:28.336
[DOOR BUZZES]

22:30.673 --> 22:32.549
- Look where you are.
- MAN: What?

22:32.717 --> 22:34.634
Ain't nothing wrong with where I'm at...

22:36.304 --> 22:38.388
Hi, Louis.

22:38.931 --> 22:42.017
- That's a nice outfit.
- Thank you.

22:43.936 --> 22:45.478
Are you trying to get me killed?

22:45.646 --> 22:48.481
You're supposed to be my wife,
not a princess.

22:49.066 --> 22:51.026
I didn't realize...

22:52.278 --> 22:54.029
Pay attention next time.

22:55.781 --> 22:57.157
[CLEARS THROAT]

23:00.578 --> 23:02.912
I ran your MO check
on serial killers here.

23:03.080 --> 23:04.247
[DOOR BUZZES]

23:04.415 --> 23:08.084
Nothing matches up.
I checked all the death certificates.

23:08.252 --> 23:11.546
All the victims died of puncture wounds
to the back of the skull.

23:12.715 --> 23:15.759
Maybe it's a serial killer,
but I'm thinking maybe it's gangs...

23:15.926 --> 23:18.011
like ritual killings.

23:18.888 --> 23:21.306
Let's concentrate on the victims.

23:22.808 --> 23:26.394
OK, the last one was Alvin Barrett.

23:27.521 --> 23:29.814
His cellmate. I'll talk to him.

23:32.068 --> 23:33.234
You did good.

23:35.446 --> 23:36.738
Thanks.

23:38.115 --> 23:39.866
I need you to get me some money.

23:40.576 --> 23:42.535
I'll have them credit your prison account.

23:42.703 --> 23:47.248
That's no good. I need real cash
to get anything done here.

23:47.416 --> 23:49.793
Inmates aren't allowed to have cash.

23:49.960 --> 23:54.005
You'll find a way to bring me
the money... easy.

23:54.632 --> 23:56.800
Louis, I don't know if I can do that.

23:58.094 --> 23:59.969
[INAUDIBLE]

24:03.432 --> 24:06.059
This is my life we're talking about.

24:08.062 --> 24:10.063
I'll get you the money.

24:19.073 --> 24:22.826
- Tell the kids Daddy loves them.
- [DOOR BUZZES]

24:25.538 --> 24:26.579
[DOOR CLOSES]

24:27.623 --> 24:31.251
I'm telling you... I won't condone it.

24:31.419 --> 24:35.130
Mr. Keane, if you won't authorize
the money, I'll give it to him myself.

24:35.923 --> 24:38.425
Don't play games with me, Ms. Beckett.

24:39.135 --> 24:41.886
You are a liaison on this case
and nothing more.

24:42.054 --> 24:44.055
Ben! Take it easy.

24:51.730 --> 24:53.231
Don't let him get to you.

24:54.942 --> 24:56.901
Another one of your lovely peers?

24:58.654 --> 24:59.654
Hi, Helen.

25:00.865 --> 25:02.907
Thank you, Rosarita. I'll do it.

25:03.701 --> 25:07.829
Oh, I stopped asking Tom
about these investigations years ago.

25:08.581 --> 25:10.748
It's all so sordid anyway.

25:10.916 --> 25:14.419
- I thought politics interested you.
- No, not any more.

25:14.587 --> 25:18.965
Since I got out of the hospital,
things have taken on a new perspective.

25:33.189 --> 25:34.189
[SMACKS LIPS]

25:34.356 --> 25:37.525
Hey, puto. Remember me, eh?

25:39.653 --> 25:42.989
Huh? Culero!

25:44.200 --> 25:46.743
I want you to meet my homey. Bruce!

25:50.289 --> 25:54.125
He likes to kick the shit
out of white trash like you, boy.

25:54.502 --> 25:55.793
Mm, culero?

25:58.047 --> 26:00.507
So what you gonna do, huh?

26:05.054 --> 26:06.429
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

26:14.939 --> 26:16.606
[GROWLS]

26:35.417 --> 26:36.876
[SCREAMS]

26:44.927 --> 26:46.386
[YELLS]

27:01.986 --> 27:03.945
[WHIRRING]

27:10.869 --> 27:15.039
- Where'd you get all those books?
- My wife. We like to read a lot.

27:15.833 --> 27:19.752
Shit. The only thing I read
is girlie-magazine letters.

27:20.713 --> 27:22.046
Get back.

27:23.591 --> 27:24.924
KONEFKE: Wait, listen to this one.

27:26.802 --> 27:31.514
"Dear Sirs, I never thought
this would happen to me

27:31.682 --> 27:36.102
but I was workin' the late shift when
this big-titted momma comes up to me..."

27:36.270 --> 27:37.604
[KONEFKE CHUCKLES]

27:39.648 --> 27:42.150
Shit, you think any of this
really happens?

27:42.318 --> 27:44.068
Uh... I Don't know.

27:44.236 --> 27:45.695
KONEFKE: It never happened to me!

27:47.114 --> 27:50.992
[CHATTERING]

28:30.949 --> 28:33.242
Hawkins, you know him?

28:35.412 --> 28:36.704
Thanks.

28:37.122 --> 28:41.167
- Hello, guys. You miss me?
- HAWKINS: It's the Lone Ranger!

28:41.377 --> 28:45.046
Hi-ho, Silver... What's up, kemo sabe?

28:46.256 --> 28:49.384
The man just waltzes right on in here

28:49.551 --> 28:52.679
and visits with the happy old Negroes.

28:57.059 --> 28:58.976
You a lobo, Burke.

28:59.144 --> 29:00.603
- I'm a lobo?
- Yeah.

29:00.771 --> 29:05.108
You know how wolves stake out
their territory, pissin' on things?

29:05.275 --> 29:07.819
I figure you pissed on
just about everything around here.

29:07.986 --> 29:09.445
[ALL CHUCKLING]

29:09.613 --> 29:12.699
- You know everything, right?
- Been here a long time.

29:12.866 --> 29:16.327
- What are you in for?
- Murder.

29:18.997 --> 29:21.124
Let me guess. You're...

29:22.292 --> 29:25.420
- You're innocent, right?
- No.

29:28.966 --> 29:31.801
I choked that son of a bitch,
sure as I'm sittin' here.

29:31.969 --> 29:33.928
Been here over ten years.

29:34.096 --> 29:38.266
That's a long time to be rollin' smokes
and countin' cockroaches.

29:41.103 --> 29:44.230
- What's that?
- Makin' shot for zip guns.

29:48.193 --> 29:49.277
Scary times.

29:49.445 --> 29:51.404
People gettin' spiked
in the head and shit.

29:53.699 --> 29:58.202
Gotta learn to defend yourself,
so you don't get dusted.

29:59.538 --> 30:03.833
You probably figure I owe you somethin'
'cause of what you did the other day.

30:05.294 --> 30:08.212
Barrett, who killed him?

30:08.380 --> 30:09.714
He was my friend.

30:10.591 --> 30:14.719
Let me tell you somethin', boy.
I don't owe you jack shit.

30:17.723 --> 30:22.101
You wanna know what happened
to your friend, see the Priest.

30:22.478 --> 30:23.644
The Priest?

30:25.230 --> 30:26.564
That's all I'm sayin'.

30:29.818 --> 30:33.196
KONEFKA: The lower you go,
the funkier it gets in this place.

30:33.363 --> 30:35.615
Down here, the guards won't even come.

30:35.783 --> 30:39.243
This guy I'm gonna introduce you to,
the Priest, man...

30:39.411 --> 30:40.411
He's part fuckin' snake!

30:40.579 --> 30:43.539
You think I'm shittin' ya,
but wait till you see his eyes.

30:43.707 --> 30:46.459
Don't look at him too long, though,
gives me the fuckin' creeps.

30:46.627 --> 30:48.461
I'm tellin' ya, you gotta
cover your ass down here,

30:48.629 --> 30:51.380
and I mean that literally, man.

30:53.050 --> 30:56.803
This is gonna blow your mind, man.
You gotta see this.

31:04.061 --> 31:05.645
[FAINT MUSIC PLAYS]

31:16.114 --> 31:19.325
<i># And when I hold your hand</i>

31:20.077 --> 31:23.996
<i># Close to my heart...</i>

31:26.250 --> 31:27.959
Go on.

31:28.126 --> 31:31.838
<i># I hope we never part</i>

31:33.465 --> 31:37.301
<i># I may not own a thing at all...</i>

31:38.178 --> 31:41.389
MAN: What are you talkin' about?
That's not the deal we made.

31:41.557 --> 31:43.933
- Priest...
- Listen!

31:44.101 --> 31:48.229
Look, I want my stuff now.

31:50.357 --> 31:52.525
KONEFKE: Like I started sayin' before...

31:53.026 --> 31:55.778
Priest, this is Burke.

31:56.363 --> 32:00.616
Yeah. I heard you went airborne on Perez.

32:02.286 --> 32:03.828
You want a lady?

32:05.581 --> 32:06.497
No.

32:06.665 --> 32:10.209
[HUFFS] He thinks he's too good for me,
Priest.

32:10.377 --> 32:13.170
What's wrong with my ladies?

32:13.338 --> 32:17.216
Nothing. I just need some help.

32:32.107 --> 32:36.736
I help lots of people.
I get Jersey hormone pills.

32:37.529 --> 32:40.239
Is that the kinda help you want?

32:40.407 --> 32:42.909
Alvin Barrett, who killed him?

32:43.076 --> 32:46.370
Someone punched a hole in his head.

32:46.538 --> 32:47.580
Why?

32:48.415 --> 32:50.708
PRIEST:
I can't just tell you these things.

32:50.876 --> 32:54.045
I give you a little, you taste it.

32:54.212 --> 32:56.547
That's how things work.

32:58.467 --> 33:02.678
You could talk to Myerson,
Barrett's former cellmate.

33:02.846 --> 33:04.764
He's in solitary now,

33:04.932 --> 33:08.851
but he works in the infirmary,
night shift.

33:09.019 --> 33:12.647
He can fill prescriptions,
if you got the money.

33:14.149 --> 33:16.817
Sure you don't wanna sample my goods?

33:18.612 --> 33:20.363
I'll take a rain check.

33:25.160 --> 33:26.702
[PRIEST CONTINUES LAUGHING]

33:32.542 --> 33:33.626
We got another one.

33:35.545 --> 33:37.046
He won't be home for dinner.

33:42.844 --> 33:45.513
- What is this?
- MAN: Goddamn medical waste.

33:52.854 --> 33:54.730
Medical waste.

34:05.492 --> 34:07.827
- You Myerson?
- Whaddaya want?

34:08.704 --> 34:10.286
I need some medicine.

34:11.081 --> 34:13.456
I got prescription drugs,
morphine and uppers.

34:13.625 --> 34:16.460
I hear you were Barrett's cellmate.
He was a good kid.

34:16.628 --> 34:18.879
- Yeah, well, he's dead now.
- Yeah, yeah.

34:19.047 --> 34:21.465
Yeah, drugs. Bad news.

34:22.551 --> 34:26.094
No way! He was as green as grass.
He never did nothin'.

34:26.263 --> 34:28.597
A convenience-store robbery and that's it.

34:29.056 --> 34:32.184
- Maybe he was in a gang, then, huh?
- I said he was clean.

34:32.351 --> 34:33.643
What are you so curious about?

34:35.772 --> 34:38.524
He was my friend. Got spiked in the head.

34:39.568 --> 34:41.318
Maybe you know who did it.

34:44.197 --> 34:47.116
- I'm not sayin' another word.
- Oh, yes, you are.

34:47.284 --> 34:48.659
Hey, fuck you.

34:51.329 --> 34:53.289
Hey, what is this?

34:54.291 --> 34:55.875
- What's this?
- Soda pop.

34:57.544 --> 35:00.296
- You're gonna drink soda pop.
- Please, man, don't!

35:00.464 --> 35:04.091
Please, man, I didn't do nothin'.
Christ, they'll kill me if I talk.

35:04.259 --> 35:07.511
- A guard let him in, not me.
- MAN: Lock up, five minutes!

35:07.679 --> 35:08.804
Move it!

35:10.891 --> 35:12.433
I'll talk to you.

35:16.021 --> 35:18.314
[SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS]

35:20.108 --> 35:21.901
[PHONE RINGS]

35:25.739 --> 35:28.449
- Hello?
- It's Burke. I've got something.

35:28.617 --> 35:30.826
Oh... Um...

35:30.994 --> 35:32.078
Hang on a sec.

35:33.497 --> 35:36.624
- OK, I'm ready.
- Barrett's cellmate is scared.

35:37.209 --> 35:39.752
Whatever's going on,
the guards are involved.

35:40.253 --> 35:42.588
I need to see the victims' files.

35:42.756 --> 35:44.590
The files haven't been transferred
to computer yet.

35:44.758 --> 35:46.592
They're still at the prison.

35:51.264 --> 35:53.849
- What are you doing?
- Right now?

35:56.269 --> 35:57.520
Eating dinner.

36:02.234 --> 36:03.442
Burke?

36:06.321 --> 36:08.614
Burke, is there anything else?

36:10.450 --> 36:12.451
I'll be in touch.

36:14.121 --> 36:16.705
- [PHONE CLICKS]
- [DIAL TONE SOUNDS]

36:19.668 --> 36:21.001
[SIGHS]

36:22.254 --> 36:24.213
Have a nice little chat?

36:28.510 --> 36:33.013
- I need the key to the records room.
- That can be arranged.

36:42.482 --> 36:45.401
- Hey! Hey!
- What?

36:47.904 --> 36:49.155
What have you got here, Hawk?

36:49.322 --> 36:52.324
A load of shirts for the reception desk.

37:04.296 --> 37:06.338
OK... you got me.

37:08.008 --> 37:10.509
Takin' some pruno
over to the guys in Storage.

37:11.511 --> 37:14.638
- You know I'm gonna have to take that.
- HAWKINS: Sure.

37:16.141 --> 37:17.766
You ever actually taste that stuff?

37:20.187 --> 37:22.855
- I don't think so.
- All right, then.

37:23.106 --> 37:25.900
MAN: Well, maybe... Let me try some.

37:57.265 --> 37:59.183
Oh, man!

37:59.351 --> 38:01.143
You gonna have to develop a taste for it.

38:01.311 --> 38:03.562
You just can't go wadin' into the shit.

38:10.820 --> 38:12.780
"SLRH..."

38:21.456 --> 38:22.790
"Arrival..."

38:23.917 --> 38:25.417
What's the connection?

38:29.756 --> 38:30.756
[SQUEAKS]

38:32.884 --> 38:35.803
- What was that?
- What was what?

39:10.964 --> 39:13.340
- I must be goin' crazy.
- Nah!

39:24.602 --> 39:27.730
Lotta old ghosts
hangin' around this place.

39:29.065 --> 39:30.065
Let's get outta here.

39:38.491 --> 39:41.493
BURKE: Only the murder victims
have the "SL" notation.

39:42.454 --> 39:45.873
The victims are brand-new,
no drugs, no gangs...

39:47.042 --> 39:49.209
all different ages and race.

39:50.920 --> 39:53.005
I can check with the mainframe system.

39:53.548 --> 39:57.176
Maybe "SL" is some sort of
departmental abbreviation.

39:57.677 --> 40:00.262
I've got the guy for you.
I've worked with him before.

40:00.430 --> 40:01.764
He's a real pro.

40:01.973 --> 40:03.766
He'll do the hacking for you.

40:05.477 --> 40:08.312
And don't tell Keane about this, OK?

40:12.692 --> 40:17.946
- [SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS]
- [COMPUTER BEEPING]

40:18.114 --> 40:21.533
- You know this is illegal, don't you?
- Sort of illegal.

40:22.619 --> 40:23.786
Do you mind?

40:24.371 --> 40:26.914
Are you kidding? I love it!

40:27.082 --> 40:31.502
See, I like to think of myself as
a renegade. You know, like a cowboy.

40:32.212 --> 40:36.215
Yeah, I'm a computer cowboy.
That's what I am.

40:48.019 --> 40:51.063
- AMANDA: Well?
- Well what? It's checking.

40:51.314 --> 40:55.484
"SL" could stand for virtually anything,
or nothing at all.

41:02.242 --> 41:05.160
So, you got a boyfriend or somethin'?

41:06.788 --> 41:10.165
The computer looks for combinations
of words beginning with "SL".

41:10.333 --> 41:13.710
Then it sees if there are any files
in the system that are named that.

41:14.421 --> 41:16.672
Shit! I'm missing Star Trek.

41:17.674 --> 41:19.425
You wanna watch Star Trek?

41:20.009 --> 41:21.343
No.

41:22.011 --> 41:24.012
All right. So...

41:25.306 --> 41:26.682
We got something here!

41:27.851 --> 41:31.645
Now we see where the files are
most commonly accessed from.

41:31.813 --> 41:33.272
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

41:33.898 --> 41:34.898
BOY: Bingo!

41:35.066 --> 41:37.192
- AMANDA: That's it. That's the file.
- Yeah.

41:40.947 --> 41:43.240
Shit! I need the password.

41:44.284 --> 41:46.076
That's OK. It's a start.

41:49.247 --> 41:53.417
Give me a day or two, and I can locate
any terminals it's been accessed from.

41:53.585 --> 41:55.502
You'd find out whose file it was.

41:56.838 --> 42:00.174
Great. Come on, I'll take you home.
Your parents'll kill me.

42:00.341 --> 42:02.050
Ah, who needs parents?

42:03.094 --> 42:05.804
We're both adults... aren't we?

42:06.639 --> 42:08.765
No. I'm an adult...

42:10.518 --> 42:11.685
and you're a kid.

42:12.228 --> 42:14.062
And your hormones are workin' overtime.

42:14.814 --> 42:16.148
Come on, I'll take you home.

42:20.904 --> 42:24.072
AMANDA: I'd rather not tell Keane
what I'm doing with the computers.

42:24.574 --> 42:27.993
Burke thinks we can get it done
a lot quicker without his interference.

42:28.495 --> 42:31.747
Detective Burke may be
interfering with your work habits.

42:31.915 --> 42:33.749
We have procedures for a reason.

42:34.918 --> 42:38.003
- I know what I'm doing, Tom.
- I hope you do.

42:38.671 --> 42:40.923
I promised your father
I'd take care of you.

42:41.758 --> 42:43.175
Don't worry.

42:46.262 --> 42:48.514
[FOOTSTEPS]

42:56.606 --> 42:59.316
Damn it! Took you long enough.

43:01.945 --> 43:03.195
You want to talk now?

43:03.363 --> 43:07.241
Look, I found out some things
about what they did to Barrett.

43:07.408 --> 43:09.409
He didn't deserve what they did to him.

43:10.578 --> 43:13.914
Look, we used to smuggle out
some drugs from overstock.

43:14.082 --> 43:15.958
Well, I was in surgery last night...

43:16.960 --> 43:19.711
Shit! Gottesman!

43:21.089 --> 43:23.298
If he finds his keys missing, I'm dead!

43:23.466 --> 43:24.716
Relax.

43:25.593 --> 43:26.802
Don't worry.

43:27.804 --> 43:30.889
I need protection 'cause another guy
got spiked last night.

43:31.057 --> 43:32.140
This is serious shit!

43:32.308 --> 43:34.518
- BURKE: Shh, quiet.
- Shit.

43:34.686 --> 43:36.853
BURKE: I've got to get
this cell key back to Priest.

43:43.486 --> 43:44.987
Protection...

43:46.072 --> 43:47.489
I need protection.

44:01.421 --> 44:02.671
[WHISPERS] Lady-killer.

44:03.506 --> 44:05.674
I just thought you'd like to know...

44:05.842 --> 44:08.343
I think somebody's gonna pay you
a visit tonight.

44:08.511 --> 44:10.762
I'd think twice about sleeping.

44:14.100 --> 44:15.142
Thanks.

44:15.310 --> 44:18.020
I just hate to see a good man go to waste.

44:23.484 --> 44:24.651
[SIGHS]

44:27.030 --> 44:28.697
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

44:28.865 --> 44:31.241
I figured out the password.

44:31.409 --> 44:34.161
I've had the computer
run word variations for hours.

44:34.329 --> 44:37.706
Of course, you know, it's a special
program that I devised myself.

44:40.209 --> 44:43.253
You know, I was reading this article
in a men's magazine

44:43.421 --> 44:47.215
about the virility of men
in their middle to late teens and...

44:47.383 --> 44:49.051
- Right.
- Just do it, Tisdale.

44:49.218 --> 44:51.053
Here we are. Right, here we go.

44:51.554 --> 44:52.846
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

44:55.099 --> 44:59.144
Morpheus was the Greek god of sleep.
I'm a whiz at mythology.

44:59.604 --> 45:01.271
Your criminals have a sense of humor.

45:03.650 --> 45:06.735
- Yes! We're in!
- AMANDA: You're kidding me.

45:07.820 --> 45:10.739
TISDALE:
No. Is there anything else you need?

45:11.324 --> 45:13.909
Print it out.
Can you make a copy of this file?

45:14.077 --> 45:16.036
- Sure I can.
- Great.

45:19.957 --> 45:21.124
AMANDA: What is it doing?

45:21.292 --> 45:23.418
TISDALE: Someone is destroying
it from the other end.

45:23.586 --> 45:25.671
- Well, stop it.
- I can't.

45:25.838 --> 45:28.090
We just have to hope
it started the print copy first.

45:35.598 --> 45:37.808
[WHIRRING]

45:45.608 --> 45:48.402
- Where was this file accessed from?
- The infirmary.

45:48.569 --> 45:53.824
I checked the other abbreviation. "HLA"
is a coding system for tissue typing.

45:53.991 --> 45:56.243
I'm checking that other point of access.

45:56.411 --> 45:58.704
It's definitely someone outside
the prison.

45:59.330 --> 46:01.081
OK, that's our key player.

46:02.458 --> 46:05.210
This is my beeper number.
Call me when you find it out.

46:05.378 --> 46:07.796
Tisdale, you... are a stud.

46:18.558 --> 46:21.393
The Sleep file contained
a list of prisoner ID numbers

46:21.561 --> 46:24.396
strung together,
along with the prisoners' blood types.

46:24.564 --> 46:27.232
Every person who was
on that list has been killed.

46:27.775 --> 46:29.067
It's a hit list.

46:29.235 --> 46:32.738
AMANDA: Exactly. Each victim had
a physical days before they were killed.

46:32.905 --> 46:37.701
Each one came up clean. You know,
no diseases, no drug addiction, nothing.

46:37.869 --> 46:41.288
I think that someone from the outside
is working with the guards.

46:42.915 --> 46:44.166
Keane.

46:45.251 --> 46:48.044
Keane would have access to the files.

46:50.131 --> 46:52.841
Burke... there's something else.

46:55.511 --> 46:57.512
Your number's next on the list.

46:58.556 --> 47:00.223
[TICKING]

47:28.044 --> 47:29.169
[GROANS]

47:38.805 --> 47:41.264
[INMATES CLAMORING]

47:41.432 --> 47:43.391
What's goin' on here?

47:44.101 --> 47:45.393
Help me.

47:46.229 --> 47:48.230
- Jesus! Grab him!
- Help me!

48:24.976 --> 48:27.686
What are you doing in my prison, hm?

48:29.480 --> 48:30.772
Somethin' wrong with your mouth?

48:30.940 --> 48:33.275
[YELLS]

48:33.442 --> 48:34.943
[GROANS]

48:49.417 --> 48:51.001
You killed Konefke.

48:54.130 --> 48:55.797
I didn't do it.

48:57.675 --> 48:59.134
I know.

49:03.222 --> 49:04.472
[GROANS]

49:09.145 --> 49:10.353
DEGRAF: Strip him!

49:11.272 --> 49:12.731
[COUGHS]

49:14.734 --> 49:17.235
<i># When I know you</i>

49:17.403 --> 49:19.487
<i># You... you!</i>

49:19.947 --> 49:21.948
<i># When I know you</i>

49:22.116 --> 49:24.492
<i># When I know you like I know... #</i>

49:32.335 --> 49:34.628
MAN: You got a big mouth, Jersey.

49:35.379 --> 49:37.464
Romie...

49:38.049 --> 49:40.675
Hey, man, I didn't say no names.

49:43.930 --> 49:46.348
I didn't say you.

49:55.399 --> 49:57.609
[WATCH TICKING]

50:14.001 --> 50:16.211
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

50:27.515 --> 50:28.556
Who's there?

50:30.476 --> 50:33.353
What's goin' on? Whaddaya want?

50:33.521 --> 50:36.314
[MAN WHISPERS] We wanna talk.
Just like Burke.

50:37.274 --> 50:39.567
I didn't talk to Burke.
I didn't say nothin'.

50:39.735 --> 50:42.070
Who said I talked to Burke? It's bullshit.

50:43.531 --> 50:44.906
What... what is that?

50:48.577 --> 50:50.036
Shit! God...

50:50.579 --> 50:52.747
Hey, wait a minute! You can't do this.

50:53.207 --> 50:56.501
You gotta hear my side.
I didn't say nothin'. Somebody's lyin'.

50:56.669 --> 50:58.211
Somebody's fuckin' Iyin' on me!

50:58.379 --> 51:01.214
Hey, I'm gonna faint.
You can't do this, man!

51:01.382 --> 51:05.385
Oh, God, just stop. Wait a minute.
Just wait one second!

51:06.512 --> 51:08.596
MAN: What did you say to Burke?

51:08.764 --> 51:10.515
Who said I talked?
How did ya find that out?

51:10.683 --> 51:12.100
That's bullshit, man!

51:12.643 --> 51:14.769
Don't! No! No!

51:14.937 --> 51:16.479
I swear to God, I didn't do it!

51:16.647 --> 51:19.733
Stop it! What are you doin'?
Are you crazy, man?

51:20.609 --> 51:23.069
Whaddaya want me to do?

51:23.529 --> 51:26.948
I'll give you anything!
Whaddaya want? Stop it! No!

51:27.116 --> 51:29.034
MAN: You're a liar, Myerson.

51:29.201 --> 51:30.660
No! Please!

51:31.162 --> 51:33.246
Please! No!

51:34.540 --> 51:36.249
[SCREAMS]

51:38.252 --> 51:40.587
[SCREAMING] Somebody! No!

51:41.756 --> 51:43.715
[ALL YELLING]

51:45.593 --> 51:46.718
[SCREAMING]

51:57.313 --> 51:58.813
AMANDA: This is ridiculous.

52:02.276 --> 52:04.152
Do you wanna see your... husband?

52:07.740 --> 52:09.699
Then bring in a female guard.

52:10.076 --> 52:12.535
None seem to be available.

52:15.873 --> 52:17.957
Up with the arms.

52:32.681 --> 52:33.723
I don't know.

52:36.268 --> 52:38.353
I'm sorry, missy...

52:38.938 --> 52:41.231
but you're gonna
have to remove your clothes.

52:44.819 --> 52:46.486
Your husband is waiting.

53:20.229 --> 53:24.607
Clean up and get dressed.
Your pretty little wife wants to see ya.

53:32.825 --> 53:34.242
[GRUNTS]

53:44.461 --> 53:48.131
- You have a half hour, Burke.
- Yeah, have a good time there, buddy.

54:04.982 --> 54:07.066
- God...
- Ah, it's OK.

54:09.236 --> 54:11.279
- Who did this to you?
- The guards.

54:11.447 --> 54:15.783
They let two prisoners into my cell.
One of them had an ice pick.

54:16.577 --> 54:18.786
At least we know
who's been spiking people.

54:21.957 --> 54:23.291
What about you?

54:26.670 --> 54:28.129
Nothing.

54:29.924 --> 54:31.257
[SIGHS]

54:37.598 --> 54:39.015
You look like hell.

54:41.101 --> 54:42.518
So do you.

54:51.946 --> 54:54.489
[QUIVERS] Um...

54:54.657 --> 54:57.575
I checked on Dr. Gottesman and, um...

55:01.413 --> 55:04.999
- And...?
- He didn't get into med school here.

55:06.210 --> 55:08.086
He went to South America.

55:08.254 --> 55:11.673
- South America?
- Uh-huh.

55:12.049 --> 55:14.342
- And um...
- And?

55:16.595 --> 55:21.140
There were... a couple of... of um...

55:23.269 --> 55:25.019
malpractice suits.

55:29.024 --> 55:30.900
[PANTING]

55:38.534 --> 55:40.326
You're so beautiful.

55:58.304 --> 55:59.804
[CHATTERING]

56:13.402 --> 56:16.988
You guys are all spooked 'cause you
think there's some big conspiracy.

56:17.156 --> 56:19.907
Priest, you know as well as I
what's goin' on, man.

56:20.659 --> 56:23.119
A brother got his brains scrambled
just last night,

56:23.287 --> 56:25.288
straight through the skull
like a piece of meat.

56:26.373 --> 56:27.915
Could be me next, could be you.

56:28.542 --> 56:31.419
So, big white superman
gonna save our asses?

56:31.587 --> 56:33.921
What makes you think we wanna be saved?

56:34.089 --> 56:37.842
Burke needs our help.
He needs a distraction.

56:48.062 --> 56:50.772
- BURKE: Good work, Hawkins.
- Thank the Priest.

56:51.148 --> 56:53.274
- Shit!
- Yeah, it's locked.

56:53.442 --> 56:56.444
- They cart medical waste day and night.
- Where does it go?

56:56.612 --> 56:59.781
I don't know. They got a special
pick-up for it. It's hazardous.

56:59.948 --> 57:01.157
Oh, yeah?

57:01.992 --> 57:04.077
Let's see what's inside. Watch your eye.

57:04.244 --> 57:06.120
Funny! Hurry up.

57:25.307 --> 57:26.516
Hold this.

57:29.853 --> 57:35.691
- [SIGHS] It's a human heart.
- Oh, God.

57:42.324 --> 57:45.576
- What's going on?
- New dude being brought in.

57:45.744 --> 57:49.497
- All this for a new fish?
- Man, this ain't no fish.

57:49.665 --> 57:51.040
This is the man!

57:53.627 --> 57:55.169
[ALL CHEERING]

57:58.757 --> 58:00.341
Sandman!

58:19.903 --> 58:21.195
[GROANS]

58:52.644 --> 58:54.520
[MOANS]

59:17.628 --> 59:19.545
Long time no see, Burke.

